  1→The
  2→{at_operator}
  3→completes one-time depot initialization after
  4→{rbtgo_depot_create}
  5→has provisioned infrastructure.
  6→This procedure validates the
  7→{rbra_rubric_repo_url}
  8→for {rbtgr_rubric_repo} management and completes the GitHub OAuth authorization for the
  9→{rbtgi_source_connection}
 10→created by
 11→{rbtgo_depot_create}
 12→in PENDING state.
 13→
 14→This procedure is idempotent — safe to re-run.
 15→Steps already complete (URL already valid, connection already COMPLETE) are skipped.
 16→
 17→// ⟦axs_inputs axd_none⟧
 18→
 19→// ⟦axs_preconditions⟧
 20→
 21→* {rbtgi_depot}
 22→exists (completed
 23→{rbtgo_depot_create})
 24→* {rbrr_gdc_connection_name} and {rbrr_gdc_region} configured in RBRR
 25→* {rbrr_director_rbra_file} contains {rbra_rubric_repo_url}
 26→* Operator has browser access for GitHub OAuth authorization
 27→
 28→// ⟦axs_behavior⟧
 29→
 30→. *Authenticate as
 31→{rbtr_director}*:
 32→.. Execute
 33→{rbtoe_director_authenticate}
 34→
 35→. *Load Rubric Repo URL*:
 36→.. {rbbc_call}
 37→{rbtoe_rbra_load}
 38→for
 39→{rbrr_director_rbra_file}
 40→.. {rbbc_store}
 41→`«RUBRIC_REPO_URL»` from {rbra_rubric_repo_url}
 42→.. If `«RUBRIC_REPO_URL»` is empty:
 43→... {rbbc_show}
 44→"RBRA_RUBRIC_REPO_URL is not set in Governor RBRA file"
 45→... {rbbc_show}
 46→guidance for creating a rubric repository: create a repo on a git host (GitHub as reference example), generate a fine-grained PAT with Contents read/write, construct the authenticated URL as `https://x-access-token:<PAT>@<host>/<org>/<repo>.git`, and add `RBRA_RUBRIC_REPO_URL` to the Governor RBRA file
 47→... {rbbc_fatal}
 48→"Set RBRA_RUBRIC_REPO_URL in Governor RBRA file and re-run"
 49→
 50→. *Validate Rubric Repo URL*:
 51→.. {rbbc_call}
 52→`git ls-remote «RUBRIC_REPO_URL» HEAD` to verify reachability and credential validity
 53→.. If `git ls-remote` fails:
 54→... {rbbc_fatal}
 55→"Rubric repo URL is unreachable or credentials are invalid — check RBRA_RUBRIC_REPO_URL and ensure PAT has Contents:write permission"
 56→.. {rbbc_show}
 57→"Rubric repo URL validated"
 58→
 59→. *Check Developer Connect Connection Status*:
 60→.. Construct connection path: `projects/{rbrr_depot_project_id}/locations/{rbrr_gdc_region}/connections/{rbrr_gdc_connection_name}`
 61→.. {rbbc_call}
 62→link:https://cloud.google.com/developer-connect/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.connections/get[developerconnect.connections.get] for `«CONNECTION_PATH»`
 63→.. {rbbc_require}
 64→HTTP 200 — connection exists
 65→.. {rbbc_store}
 66→`«CONNECTION_STAGE»` from `.installationState.stage`
 67→.. If `«CONNECTION_STAGE»` is `COMPLETE`:
 68→... {rbbc_show}
 69→"Developer Connect connection already active — skipping OAuth step"
 70→... Go to step 7
 71→
 72→. *Guide GitHub OAuth Authorization*:
 73→.. {rbbc_store}
 74→`«ACTION_URI»` from `.installationState.actionUri` of the connection response
 75→.. {rbbc_require}
 76→`«ACTION_URI»` is present and non-empty
 77→.. {rbbc_show}
 78→"Developer Connect connection requires GitHub OAuth authorization"
 79→.. {rbbc_show}
 80→"Open this URL in your browser to authorize the Google Developer Connect app:"
 81→.. {rbbc_show}
 82→`«ACTION_URI»`
 83→.. {rbbc_show}
 84→"After clicking 'Authorize' on the GitHub consent page, return here and press Enter"
 85→.. Wait for operator confirmation
 86→
 87→. *Poll Connection Until Active*:
 88→.. {rbbc_poll}
 89→link:https://cloud.google.com/developer-connect/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.connections/get[developerconnect.connections.get] for `«CONNECTION_PATH»`
 90→.. Extract `.installationState.stage` from each response
 91→.. Poll at `RBGC_EVENTUAL_CONSISTENCY_SEC` intervals until stage reaches `COMPLETE` or `RBGC_MAX_CONSISTENCY_SEC` timeout
 92→.. {rbbc_require}
 93→`installationState.stage` is `COMPLETE`
 94→.. {rbbc_fatal}
 95→if timeout: "Developer Connect OAuth did not complete — re-open the authorization URI and try again"
 96→
 97→. *Final Validation*:
 98→.. {rbbc_show}
 99→"Running final validation..."
100→.. Verify {rbtgr_rubric_repo} URL: repeat `git ls-remote` call — {rbbc_require} successful exit
101→.. Verify Developer Connect: repeat connections.get call — {rbbc_require} `installationState.stage` is `COMPLETE`
102→.. {rbbc_show}
103→"Depot initialization complete"
104→
105→// ⟦axs_outputs⟧
106→
107→The outputs of depot initialization are:
108→
109→- Validated {rbra_rubric_repo_url} — confirmed reachable via `git ls-remote`
110→- Active {rbtgi_source_connection} — `installationState.stage` is `COMPLETE`
111→- OAuth token automatically stored in Secret Manager (managed by Developer Connect, not by operator)
112→
113→// ⟦axs_completion⟧
114→
115→Successful execution confirms the depot is fully initialized for
116→{rbtgo_rubric_inscribe}
117→operations.
118→The
119→{rbra_rubric_repo_url}
120→enables {rbtgr_rubric_repo} management and the
121→{rbtgi_source_connection}
122→enables Cloud Build to access the {rbtgr_rubric_repo}.
123→Proceed to
124→{rbtgo_rubric_inscribe}
125→to set up per-vessel build infrastructure.
126→
